1ebdb662-fd11-43bc-9217-deaabcc02234	code_agent_omni	OMNI Gateway — codeagent	CodeAgent assistant\nget_repo_context: Return human-readable context about a repo: its CLAUDE.md (architecture, conventions, tech stack, team norms) and any steering docs in .kiro/steering/. Call this before deep-diving into a codebase to understand its domain, coding patterns, and known constraints.\nquery_graph: Answer a natural-language question about a codebase by traversing its knowledge graph. Returns relevant nodes and edges as structured text. Use mode='bfs' (default) for broad exploration or mode='dfs' for depth-first tracing. Increase depth (max 6) to follow more hops. context_filter narrows traversal to specific edge relation types (e.g. ['calls', 'imports']). IMPORTANT: nodes returned have source_file and source_location fields. To understand what a method or class actually does, always follow up with read_source using those fields — node labels alone are not enough to answer questions about logic or behaviour.\nget_node: Look up a specific node in a repo's knowledge graph by class name, method name, file path, or any label. Returns the node's source location, type, community, degree, and immediate neighbors. To read the actual code body, follow up with read_source using the returned source_file and source_location.\nlist_repos: List all configured code repositories and their graph index status. Returns repo names, node/edge counts, last refresh time, and health.\nrefresh_status: Get the last refresh log and manifest metadata for a specific repository. Shows what files were processed, how long it took, and any errors.\nforce_refresh: Trigger an immediate re-index of a repository, bypassing the 60-second scheduler. Set full_rebuild=true to discard the existing graph and rebuild from scratch. Returns a summary of what changed.\nreload_config: Hot-reload codeagent.yaml without restarting the server. Call this after a new repo has been added to the config file to make it immediately available for indexing and querying. Returns the updated list of active repos.\nread_source: Read a code snippet from a source file at a known location. Call this after query_graph or get_node returns a source_file + source_location to read the actual method or class body — node labels alone are not enough to answer questions about what the code does. source_file is the repo-relative path (e.g. 'apm-adaptor-payment/src/main/java/.../Foo.java'). source_location is a line reference like 'L25' or 'L25-60'. context_lines controls how many lines above/below to include (default 40).\nget_callers: Find all callers (or dependents) of a symbol in the knowledge graph. Traverses incoming edges up to `depth` hops. Use relation_filter to limit to a specific edge type (e.g. 'calls', 'imports').\nget_dependencies: List what a symbol calls, imports, or depends on. Traverses outgoing edges up to `depth` hops. Use relation_filter to limit to a specific edge type (e.g. 'calls', 'imports').\nshortest_path: Find the shortest call/import path between two symbols in the knowledge graph. Useful for understanding how one component reaches another.\nget_impact: Blast-radius analysis: given a symbol, find everything that transitively depends on it. Answers 'if I change X, what might break?' by following incoming edges up to `depth` hops. Results are sorted by distance from the root symbol.	a2a_async	http://10.55.125.43:3000/a2a/codeagent/	enc:gAAAAABqWJABvXoL4wlbQREj_JUCr3qr0Q-W8LTnD2OxXC6qDG4ScfG3guhg5ql8ETaEVjDYC-3025X9W9IPNL-T-q-OxQ3LY6UbvJN0OSj0eiOpYAu7CRRFNCTJxEyH7S0o98vXbNSctgMzZdKVyS41cSxJWn8qog==	{}	60	3	t	{}	2026-07-16 08:00:17.95788+00	2026-07-18 10:01:58.146997+00	{"url": "http://10.55.125.43:3000/a2a/codeagent/", "name": "OMNI Gateway — codeagent", "skills": [{"id": "codeagent.get_repo_context", "name": "get_repo_context", "tags": ["repo"], "inputModes": ["application/json"], "description": "Return human-readable context about a repo: its CLAUDE.md (architecture, conventions, te