f14db1de-bd21-4666-addc-c8b7a30619f4	pyhelper	OMNI Gateway — pyhelper	OMNI agentic gateway: pyhelper\ncompare_smoke_session: Compare all before/after CSV file pairs in a smoke test session. Returns PASSED if files are identical, FAILED with a diff summary if not. Rows are matched by content (not position) to avoid false positives when a row is inserted or deleted. Key columns for cell-level diffs are auto-detected from the CSV headers.\ndownload_smoke_file_from_s3: Download a file from S3 into the smoke session folder (before/after). The S3 key is always built from the provided fields. FILE_TYPE is inferred in this priority order: (1) GL document type present → GL; (2) currency present (e.g. GBP, USD) → GROSS_INVOICE; (3) contract contains 'CP' → PARTNER_STATEMENT; (4) default → MERCHANT_STATEMENT. Always use the FULL contract identifier (e.g. '001-CM-000847', NOT just '000847'). partner_contract can be a contract number (e.g. '001-CP-000308') or the word 'Direct' for direct merchants. For GL files: pass gl_document_type (e.g. 'GL_EXTRACTS', 'GL_FX', 'GL_FX_VISA', 'GL_INTERBRANCH') and financial_institution (e.g. '0001', '0002', 'Malta') to build the key correctly. \nfind_file_in_downloads: Search the server resources folder for a smoke test file matching the given type and optional requirements. Returns the most recently modified matching file, or 'found: false' if none exists. Only available in the 'before' phase — after deployment, use download_smoke_file_from_s3 instead.\nsave_existing_file_as_smoke: Copy a local file (found via find_file_in_downloads) into the smoke session folder under 'before'. Only available in the 'before' phase — after deployment, use download_smoke_file_from_s3 instead.\nfind_file_in_db: Query the metadata database for a file matching the given criteria. All filters are optional — omit any you don't need. If multiple rows match, one is chosen at random.\ncreate_smoke_session: Create a new smoke test session. Returns session_id and the bef